  <b>Git Contributors and Deploy Permissions</b>
  <p>The Git Contributors project was one of the first big documentation efforts I was in charge of while at Netlify. Git Contributors was a new, paid user role. Teams could add non-team members to their teams as Git Contributors, granting them temporary permission to trigger builds, deploys, or Deploy Previews. I audited the current documentation and ensured that I not only covered what Git Contributors were and how to add them, but also the core functionality of what working with Git Contributors actually meant for a Netlify team.</p>
