  <b>Docs homepage redesign</b>
  <p>While at Netlify, I led a project to completely revamp our Docs homepage. The project aimed to improve the quality and user experience of our site. We wanted to align with the Netlify branding for a seamless experience and set the stage for further improvements. Our goal was to decrease the average time spent on the home page so users could quickly find what the need and move forward.</p>
  <p>The project started with digging into the relevant data in Google Analytics to figure out how long users are spending on the home page and the common pages they visit after reaching the page. I then collaborated with one of our designers to create a plan, and checked in with our Marketing team to ensure our branding was cohesive. During the process I decided to leverage Sanity to create content blocks that could be easily updated by our docs team members.</p>
